he fit between the Bank's lending program and its development objectives; concepts, its vision of development and anti-poverty strategy; and power, which includes the Bank's relationships with member countries and the wider public, as well as structures of internal governance and accountability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLoans, ForeignzDeveloping countriesvCongresses. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.1 aPincus, Jonathan R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWinters, Jeffrey A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172949240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501729492423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501729492/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles